ted positive for an anabolic steroid</a> on 16 August when he was competing for Astana’s development team at the Tour de l’Ain. The 20-year-old rider finished 15th. Fedosseyev has yet to request a B sample test.</p> <p>The case was announced on Tuesday while the UCI licence commission reviewed Astana’s application to retain top-tier World Tour status next season.</p> <p>The Kazakh government-backed team’s star rider is the <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/jul/27/vincenzo-nibali-tour-de-france-win\" title=\"\">Tour de France winner Vincenzo Nibali of Italy</a>. In recent weeks Nibali’s team-mates Maxim and Valentin Iglinskiy have tested positive for EPO, and Ilya Davidenok tested positive for steroids. Last week another Astana development rider, <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/nov/19/astana-scandal-rider-fails-doping-test\" title=\"\">Victor Okishev, was provisionally suspended after testing positive for an anabolic steroid</a>.</p>","headline":"Astana’s Artur Fedosseyev provisionally suspended by UCI for doping","trailText":"The International Cycling Union has provisionally suspended Artur Fedosseyev after he tested positive for an anabolic steroid","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Sport/Pix/pictures/2014/11/26/1417023860240/Astana-team-in-action-dur-006.jpg","wordcount":"139","commentable":"false","byline":"Agencies","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-11-29T17:47:17Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/nov/26/astana-artur-fedosseyev-suspended-uci-doping","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/2014/nov/26/astana-artur-fedosseyev-suspended-uci-doping","tags":[{"id":"sport/uci","webTitle":"UCI (Union Cycliste Internationale)","type":"keyword","sectionId":"sport","sectionName":"Sport","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/uci","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/uci","references":[]},{"id":"sport/cycling","webTitle":"Cycling","type":"keyword","